  "prompt": "When entering the US will I be detained for a bench warrant?",
  "response": "When entering the US, it is possible to be detained for an outstanding bench warrant. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) has access to law enforcement databases and can check for active warrants. If a warrant is found, you may be:\n\n1. Detained at the port of entry\n2. Turned over to local law enforcement\n3. Potentially arrested\n\nHowever, the outcome depends on:\n- The type and severity of the warrant\n- The jurisdiction\n- Specific circumstances\n\nFor the most accurate advice, consult a local attorney who can review your specific situation.",
